  <a href="#1" id="1">
   THE STORY OF ROBERT MAXWELL
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   MR MICHAEL STONEY, a senior executive in a number of Maxwell companies, is named as one of three people primarily responsible for more than Pounds 180m of 'unusual' payments from Mirror Group Newspapers bank accounts during the last financial year, according to the chairman's statement released with MGN accounts on June 23, 1992.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   Mr Kevin Maxwell and Mr Ian Maxwell, two sons of the late Robert Maxwell, are named as the other two people most involved in these transactions.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   Mr Kevin Maxwell and Mr Stoney refused to provide MGN with information, the statement says.
  </a>
